  "description": [
    "278 The Journalist DEVOTED TO ALL WHO MAKE OR READ NEWSPAPERS ALLAN FORMAN Editor Published by The Journalist Publishing Company 20 Liberty Street New York Subscription Four Dollars a Year Six Months Two Dollars Three Months One Dollar Remit by express money order draft P O order or registered letter Day of Publication SATURDAY Founded March 22 1884 Trade AgentsThe American News Company Editors or publishers requiring the services of reporters editors artists or literary services ofany kind can secure the same by addressing the Editor of The Journalist Entered at the New York Postoffice at secondclass rates We will not Exchange with any Paper NEWSPAPERS ARE MIXED UP OVER A BILLION The newspapers have been much mixed during the week over a matter of A Billion of Business It appears that the news got abroad that Mr Alexander the new president of the Equitable Life Assurance Society intended on the occasion of the Fortieth Anniversary of the institution in July to announce if possible A Billion of Insur ance in force The New York Life people heard of this and concluded that about June i that institution would be ready to announce a Billion at risk Meantime The Mutual"
